  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-01 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package contains an orphan claim (W-EP-01): the bindsClaim target carries a thorough prose description referencing validation studies and uncertainty quantification work, but the structured prov:wasDerivedFrom derivation link to any Evidence node is absent, leaving the claim epistemically unsupported in the formal graph.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Not accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-credibility",
