      "rationale": "GCI 2.7% on fine-to-medium pair; Richardson extrapolation applied across four mesh levels; asymptotic ratio 1.02 confirming convergence. Achieved level 3 against required level 4 due to absence of temporal discretization error quantification for transient spin-up."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions documented with measurement uncertainty; inlet velocity profiles characterised; fluid temperature and viscosity measured and reported.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental dataset provides flow rate and pressure rise but inlet velocity profile reconstructed from bulk flow assumption rather than measured. Blood analogue viscosity reported as nominal value without temperature correction. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., NRMSE, E-value) computed with experimental uncertainty bounds; comparison covers all five operating points; systematic bias characterised.",
      "rationale": "NRMSE 18.3% computed across five operating points; systematic over-prediction at high speed conditions (+22%) not fully explained. Experimental uncertainty bounds not propagated into comparison metric. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
