      "acceptanceCriteria": "Primary QoI (NIH) directly maps to clinical hemolysis threshold; secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) assessed for sensitivity to model parameters.",
      "rationale": "NIH directly maps to clinical threshold. Shear stress distribution characterised. Residence time distribution computed but sensitivity analysis incomplete for inlet profile uncertainty. Achieved level 3 against required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation geometry identical or demonstrably similar to COU device; operating conditions span COU envelope; blood analogue properties matched to human blood within stated tolerance.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic pump geometry which approximates but is not identical to the COU device. Operating conditions span 3 of 5 COU points; two high-flow conditions not covered by validation dataset. Blood analogue (glycerol-water) viscosity matched within 8%. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
    },
