    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model achieves sufficient credibility for the stated VAD COU based on the comprehensive body of validation evidence described in the bindsClaim assertion, including mesh convergence studies, PIV velocity comparisons, absolute NIH validation against FDA pump data, and Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification. All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated. While achieved levels fall below required levels across multiple factors, the overall evidence base — as described in the claim — is judged adequate for the intended regulatory submission. The claim references extensive supporting work and the assessment team is satisfied that the model predictions are fit for purpose.",
